text: Thomas Foster (c.1720-65), of Elim, Jamaica, and Egham House, Surrey, was an English politician. He was a Member (MP) of the Parliament of England for Bossiney 1741 and 1742 to 1747 and for Dorchester 1761 to 1765.http://www.historyofparliamentonline.org/volume/1715-1754/member/foster- thomas-1720-65 ==References== Category:1720 births Category:1765 deaths Category:People from Surrey Category:Members of the Parliament of Great Britain for English constituencies
